  "term": "thm:limsup-largest-subsequential-limit",
  "kind": "Theorem",
  "title": "Limsup Is the Largest Subsequential Limit",
  "root": "",
  "statement": "Let $(x_n)$ be a bounded real sequence, and let\n$S=\\limsup_{n\\to\\infty}x_n$. Then $S$ is a subsequential limit of\n$(x_n)$, and every subsequential limit of $(x_n)$ is less than or equal\nto $S$.",
